column3: (file format explainer)->
column4:
Localization files are formatted like CSV so they can be easily edited,
however formatting has strict rules for easy parsing. Most of these rules
are already handled by Excel / Libre / etc., so you don't have to worry
about them in normal usage. However, if your localization file seems to
be corrupted, these rules may be helpful for debugging purposes...
- The first 4 rows can be arbitrarily long
  - The first cell of first row is used to store this block of instruction
    text
  - The first 3 cells of the fourth row is used as headers
  - All other cells in the first and fourth rows are ignored
  - Columns in the second row alternate between property and value (ex.
    ' foo | 1 | bar | 3.5 | ... '
    - Any whitespaces before and after the property name are ignored
  - Columns in the third row are exclusively comments for properties in the
    second row
- Every following line can include any number of cells, but only the
  first four will be parsed (you can use the rest as comments if needed)
  - The fourth column is an optional metadata column

column3: NonDialogueFontScale

column1: Set to 1 allow the parser to read this file, otherwise it will be skipped and the default English localization will be used as fallback
column3: Float value that scales font size of all non-dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column5: Float value that scales font size of all dialogue text, 1.0 for full size.
column7: The author(s) of this file, will appear in credits

column2: The line's fixed up! Great job runt. We just need those darn <#e6e639>explosives</color> now.
column3: 铁轨修好了!好样的小子.我门只缺<#e6e639>爆炸物</color>了.

column2: Yah got it all! I'll get Drew to move his dump truck.
column3: 万事俱备!我来让德鲁把他的卡车移开.

column2: Good luck out there space man.
column3: 祝你好运,太空人.

column2: Most of the robots in the factory have gotten a lot friendlier since teaming together to save you.
column3: 工厂里的机器人变得友善了--自从它们为了救你联合起来.

column2: Something about the desperation to save you snapped us all out of it.
column3: 我们不知怎么变得团结一致.

column2: Apparently this is their sense of humor... just... play along I guess.
column3: 也许这是它们的幽默吧...

column2: We're the anti-anti-pooping union!
column3: 我们是反-反-拉屎同盟!

column2: Just hold it in!
column3: 憋住!

column2: No poop on company time! Not efficient!
column3: 不准上班时间拉屎!没有效率!

column2: Do it at home!
column3: 回家去拉!

column2: I just really like the time to myself...
column3: 我只是喜欢把时间留给自己...

column2: H- Hello? Who are you?
column3: 你,你好?你是谁?

column2: Don't mind me, I'm not from around here either.
column3: 哦,我也不是本地人.

column2: We've finally finished unpacking our research equipment.
column3: 研究仪器终于拆出来了.

column2: I'm investigating how entangles items behave in various circumstances.
column3: 我们在研究相互[时空纠缠]的物品.

column2: Whatttt, you wanted that gem? But it's already a part of the experiment!
column3: 什么,你想要那颗[宝石]?那可是实验需要的!

column2: We managed to entangle a conductive bob somewhere, it should help in finishing this.
column3: 我们成功纠缠住了一个[导电球],应该对完成实验有些帮助.

column2: Aha, this appears to be the conductive bob from the present.
column3: 啊哈,这看起来是[现在]的导电球.

column2: Aha, this appears to be the conductive bob from the past.
column3: 啊哈,这看起来是[过去]的导电球.

column2: How fascinating! Moving the past item affects its future self.
column3: 啊哈,这看起来是[未来]的导电球.

column2: I will continue these expirments. We must understand it all.
column3: 我们需要继续实验!

column2: Har har har these explosives are so *powerful*
column3: 哼哼哼,这些炸药太*劲爆*了

column2: Haha get it, they're such a *blast*
column3: 哈哈,懂吗?它们很有*冲击力*

column2: Woah.
column3: 哇.

column2: That one really *knocked my socks off*
column3: 那一个真的让我*一惊一炸*.

column2: You're back! It's always a *blast* to have you around.
column3: 你回来了!你已经不是*初来炸到*了.

column2: We've got all the gems? Let's bring them back!
column3: 我们集齐全部的水晶了?是时候把它们带回去了.

column2: You know trespassing is a crime right? Right? Please say something.
column3: 你知道我们不该穿过这里的吧...

column2: They doing some wild stuff here dude. You know, science.
column3: 他们在搞一些很[疯狂]的事情.你懂的,科学!

column2: It's been so long since I've seen Barron... it'd probably be too awkward anyways.
column3: 我很久没跟大亨打过招呼了...也许会很尴尬,算了.

column2: War? Yeah, I'm a pro at RPS Tactics what about it?
column3: 打仗?我在[穿越RPS洲精英]里可是大师段位!这对我小菜一碟!

column2: This place is ripe with artifacts!
column3: 这里的遗物琳琅满目!

column2: Groovy!
column3: 哇塞!

column2: For people with time travel you'd think they'd have more stuff.
column3: 我感觉...他作为一个时间旅行者,应该有更多宝物...

column2: He wants that much money?! MRI doesn't even have that kind of cash.
column3: 他想要那么多钱?就连MRI也没有那么多经费.

column2: So... how's <var>Cat</var> doing?
column3: 话说...<var>Cat</var>怎样了?

column2: Are we there yet?
column3: 我们到了吗?

column2: I wonder what the Archeologist is up to.
column3: 不知道考古学家现在在干什么.

column2: Woah!
column3: 哇!

column2: What in the- watch where you're dropping that thing!
column3: 小心点!不要乱扔那个东西!

column2: Explosives..?
column3: 爆炸物...?

column2: Yeahhh I'm cool off dice for the time being.
column3: 哈哈...也许我应该把骰子停一停了...

column2: One day, I'll be the king of something like this.
column3: 总有一天,我会当上这样的国王.

column2: Woah, who's this handsome devil.
column3: 哇,这个帅哥是谁~

column2: Woah woah woah, why are there so many colors here?
column3: 哇哇哇,为什么这里五颜六色的?

column2: This is... mystical...
column3: 这很...神秘...

column2: Heh, I'm sure I can turn on the laser if we really need to.
column3: 呃,我很确定我们可以等到[真正需要]这个激光的时候再把它打开.

column2: That crystal... it's been here for a thousand years?!
column3: 那块水晶...它在这里保存了一千年?!

column2: Didn't they dig this up recently? The Archeologist was going off about it.
column3: 他们不是最近才把它挖出来的吗?考古学家跟我说过,不过我忘了一大半了.

column2: I heard you plan on going to space... I guess that's pretty cool.
column3: 我听说你计划上太空...我猜那还挺酷的.

column2: This is it, huh? The point of no return.
column3: 已经没有回头路了,是么?

column2: Watch out!! Haha just kidding it's already dead.
column3: 小心!!哈哈,逗你玩~它已经死了.

column2: I'll never get used to that...
column3: 我不可能适应这个...

column2: I think I'm gonna barf.
column3: 我有点...反胃...

column2: <var>MiscChadFollowPlayerChirp</var>
column3: <var>MiscChadFollowPlayerChirp</var>

column2: You have entered the closet.
column3: 你进入了衣柜.

column2: Oh. my. GOD. WHO PUT A GATE ON THE BATHROOM DOOR.
column3: 我·的·天!谁把厕所门锁上了!

column2: GET OUTTTTTTTT
column3: 锁门的混蛋!给我滚出来!!

column2: I almost died thank GOD you opened that door.
column3: 我几乎就要完蛋了,谢谢你把门打开.

column2: I would have done vile things to the floor outside the office.
column3: 要是你没有来,我也许会做一些"违背员工准则"的事情...

column2: Straight animal. Untamed. Wild. Unhinged.
column3: 像一只野兽一样的.

column2: You would have seen a different side of me, let me tell you.
column3: 你不会想见到的"我的那一面"的.

column2: It looks like you're stuck! Let me help you out.
column3: 你看起来卡住了!让我来帮你解开~

column2: Tada!
column3: 当当~

column2: Sorry, my dump truck is blocking the way up north.
column3: 抱歉,我的货车把向北的路挡住了.

column2: The foreman told me to park my big dump truck right here.
column3: 那个工头说我必须把火车停在这里.

column2: I can move my dump truck once he gives the all clear.
column3: 我当然可以把车移开--但是我需要工头给的许可.

column2: Move? Well, we need to get the <#e6e639>explosives</color> from the military and <#c060c0>crystals</color> from the mountains.
column3: 挪开?呃,我们需要大山那边的<#c060c0>水晶</color>和军队那边的<#e6e639>爆炸物</color>.

column2: The military conflict should be taking place south of the Factory.
column3: 军队在工厂南边忙着呢.

column2: Move? Well, we still need the <#c060c0>crystals</color> from the mountains.
column3: 挪开?呃,我们还需要大山那边的<#c060c0>水晶</color>.

column2: I'd check north of the Chloro Caves. Follow the rail line East.
column3: 我如果是你的话,回去北边的水帘洞看看.跟着铁轨向东.

column2: Move? Well, we still need to get the <#e6e639>explosives</color> from the military.
column3: 挪开?呃,我们还需要军队那边的<#e6e639>爆炸物</color>.

column2: The military conflict should be taking place south of the Factory.
column3: 军队在工厂南边忙着呢.

column2: Something went wrong... you should be allowed to pass. Please tell a dev!
column3: 出问题了!你应该被允许通过的...请联系开发者!

column2: Ship all rocket materials to MRI via this road.
column3: 用这条路运送火箭材料到MRI.

column2: See that Conductive Bob on the ground? That might be useful to you.
column3: 那个地上的[导电球]也许对你有帮助.

column2: Some human got it stuck in there though.
column3: 好像有个人类把它卡在那里了.

column2: How are we going to get that bob back now?
column3: 我们该怎么把导电球取回来?

column2: Wait. You weren't supposed to do that.
column3: 等等,你不该那么做的.

column2: You were supposed to use the anchor... below the fence... you know what nevermind.
column3: 你应该用船锚...在栏杆下面...呃...不管了.

column2: Treat that Conductive Bob safe now, there's only one of them.
column3: 小心保护那个导电球,我们只有那一个了!

column2: You have your own conductor... but...
column3: 你拿到了导电球...但是...

column2: There should be a way to get <wavy>both</wavy> the Conductive Bob and the Anchor free from there.
column3: 有没有办法把导电球和船锚<wavy>都</wavy>搬出去呢?

column2: Hey pal.
column3: 嘿伙计.

column2: It appears that you are stuck.
column3: 看起来你卡住了.

column2: This was not part of the prototcol.
column3: 这不是协议的一部分.

column2: Remember, this is your fault.
column3: 记住了,这完全是你的错.

column2: INTIATING ELECTRIFICATION PROCEDURE
column3: 开启电击程序--

column2: Ow. That hurt.
column3: 哦,好疼.

column2: I hope you're happy.
column3: 开心了吗?

column2: Fantastic work. Couldn't have done it better myself.
column3: 完美.

column2: Who decided to power this conveyor with a button?
column3: 谁决定该用[按钮]控制这个传送带的?

column2: Why couldn't we use a lever like every other conveyor?
column3: 所有其他的传送带用的都是控制杆!

column2: Really.
column3: 真的.

column2: What did you think would happen.
column3: 你刚才以为能发生什么?

column2: Try using that uh... scroll or something.
column3: 你试试那个...卷轴之类的.

column2: This whole place is so inconvenient.
column3: 这里太不方便了.

column2: I suppose this area does have its charm though.
column3: 也许这里还不错.

column2: Sorry but I uh... I done broke the Timed Gate's screen up there...
column3: 抱歉...呃...我把时限门的屏幕搞坏了...

column2: It still works though! Ya just can't see the screen.
column3: 它还能工作!就是少了个屏幕.

column2: I can't get used to these new fangled technologies.
column3: 我搞不懂这些新技术.

column2: Oh! Ya turned it on.
column3: 哦!你把它打开了.

column2: That gate right there's got three inputs. Try powerin' them all.
column3: 那个大门有三个接口.试着把它们一起激活.

column2: Yer a smart cookie! That gate should stay open fer the rest of the day now.
column3: 你这个聪明蛋!大门应该可以一直开着了.

column2: Wanna do the other one too while yer at it?
column3: 你能在那边另一扇门上照做一遍吗?

column2: Phew, that's enough timed gate fer me.
column3: *叹气*我受够这些时限门了.

column2: Great to see we got crystals again!
column3: 我们又有水晶了!不错.

column2: Who ah- wait a secawnd, Bab tawld me about you.
column3: 谁?哦--等等,鲍勃跟我提过你.

column2: You know, bab the bahtendah? said you's the guy putting the wawld back togethah.
column3: 就是那个开酒馆的鲍勃,你认识的.他说有个小探险家在修复世界!

column2: Tell you what, my factory heeuh is in disahray. I think we can help each othah.
column3: 我的工厂现在一团乱.

column2: The egg heads at the MRI cawntracted us for a rocket, but still need an astronawt.
column3: MRI那边的"蛋脑壳"们雇我们建一个火箭,但是还缺一个宇航员.

column2: We need the factory fixed, some crystal gem fuel, and explosives to finish it.
column3: 如果你能帮我们修好工厂,找到一些[水晶燃料],还有一些[爆炸物]...

column2: Then... maybe we can hook you up.
column3: 也许我们能推荐由你来驾驶它...听着怎么样?

column2: I'll go ask them in a bit and i'll check in on youh prawgress latah.
column3: 成交!我先去和MRI谈一谈,一会来查收你的成果.

column2: Buttons and wires are everywhere, huh.
column3: 到处都是按钮和电缆.

column2: Those new robots are causing quite the stir here too.
column3: 这些新来的机器人到处捣乱...

column2: Personally, I miss the mines.
column3: 要问我,我还是想念矿洞.

column2: Oh, someone told me the number on screen is how many moves you have left.
column3: 哦,有人告诉我屏幕上的数字是你[剩下的步数].

column2: Frankly, I have no idea what that means...
column3: 说实话,我根本不知道他在说什么...

column2: I'm just waiting for when the crystals finally come back from the mines.
column3: 我在等他们把大山那边的水晶矿"重新续上".

column2: Well, that's all done now.
column3: 工厂终于拼齐了.

column2: Time to fix up things in the Crystal Mines, eh?
column3: 该修复水晶矿洞了?
